The advantages of temperate living, in its effects both on the . body and the mind, are set forth in this satire with much truth and simplicity. They are represented as coming from an un- lettered pensant, who delivers them without affectation, as the re- sult of his own experience and observation. 1. Boni .- ‘my good friends.’
